<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note22" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Sertorius*.html#ref22
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">22</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Sertorius*.html#25.4
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chapter xxv.4</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note23" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Sertorius*.html#ref23
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">23</A>
Spain was divided into two provinces, Hispania Citerior <I>(Hither)</I> and Hispania Ulterior <I>(Further)</I>, or Eastern and Western Spain. Fufidius was <SPAN CLASS="whole">pro-consul</SPAN> of Western Spain.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note24" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Sertorius*.html#ref24
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">24</A>
<I>Cf.</I> the
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Pompey*.html#17.2
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Pompey</I>, xvii.2</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note25" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Sertorius*.html#ref25
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">25</A>
The story is told also in Valerius Maximus,
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Valerius_Maximus/7*.html#3.6
	"TARGET="Valerius_Maximus"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="small">VII</SPAN>.3.6</A>.

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
	<P CLASS="b0 a0">
Thayer's Note: As well as in the Stratagems of Frontinus
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/Strategemata/1*.html#10.1
	"TARGET="Frontinus_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,1,WIDTH,165)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(<SPAN CLASS="small">I</SPAN>.<SPAN CLASS="smaller">X</SPAN>.1)</A>, another writer earlier than Plutarch.
	</DIV>


