	<HR CLASS="endnotes"><A ID="endnotes_T"></A>
	<H2>
Thayer's Notes:
	</H2>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:Tingis" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Sertorius*.html#ref:Tingis
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">a</A>
Tangier, Morocco, founded by the Phoenicians many years before this story, has a long association with the Pillars of Hercules.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:Roman_fossil_hunters" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Sertorius*.html#ref:Roman_fossil_hunters
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">b</A>
Ancient literature and medieval churches are full of bones of giants, many of which turn out to be mammoth or dinosaur remains. In May 2000 Adrienne Mayor published her seminal book, <I>The First Fossil Hunters</I>, in which she laid out the evidence for fossil collection in Antiquity; and among the evidence this account of Sertorius' viewing figures prominently. See
	<A HREF="
http://www.reocities.com/stegob/mayorarticle.html
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
this page
	</A>
for further fascinating details.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:Mellaria" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Sertorius*.html#ref:Mellaria
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">c</A>
The modern Spanish town of Melilla, an enclave on the African coast of the Straits of Gibraltar.



